    },
    {
      "id": "e55c18e09ddfc42a322e050a27459a2554dee7dd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-01 10:06:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI actually got the same question, could you please explain how rq_req_unlink resolves issue here?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "8d84fbc35713d74e741843cd7d888d742d8a14e7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-05 11:47:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nit's very easy - to mark request unlinked we need unlink both buffers and bulk (if need). So we can't do anything until LNet unlink event isn't received. \nso we can't resend or process reply until both buffers and bulk unlinked,\nand we can't shutdown client because client_disconnect_export->ptlrpc_invalidate_import will abort in flith (ptlrpc_deactivate_import->abort_in_flight) and wait until requests will finished (aka called interpret) via \n                rc = l_wait_event(imp->imp_recovery_waitq,\n                                  (cfs_atomic_read(&imp->imp_inflight) == 0),\n                                  &lwi);\n\nit's easy.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1b002c0b3685d19d778c4106cfc8e0dc7276b9a2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-05 11:51:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nin general it's bug in LNet code. LNet commit MD on initial LNetGet / LNetPut call, but we don't connect such buffer to the network driver so able to unlink buffer quickly, but LNet mark MD busy and stop sending event and unlink buffer.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7614203182d77ceed5d4a1b3902a7f227c3ca096",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-05 12:49:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n/* unlink from net because we are going to\n                         * swab in-place of reply buffer */\n                        unregistered = ptlrpc_unregister_reply(req, 1);\n                        if (!unregistered)\n                                continue;\n\n\nthis call block access to the request buffer (initial request buffer) if it's pined in LNet but LNet don't release it reference, but ptlrpc may change buffer while LNet transmit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d0b0b2db1bde92cd2dfb9af245c016aa82ef6328",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
