    {
      "id": "c91f0a878fe7bfd445d5bbf864c7a3991d566d32",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-05 15:35:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nsorry I still don't understand, even with this new flag rq_req_unlink, as far as I can see from this patch, it's (still) only unset by request_out_callback(), which is only called after LNet/LND has released reference on MD of request buffer? did I miss something here?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "592a3cdd00c2bbc9794034c9b4f4b83d2aab8553",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-05 19:30:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nlook to background https://projectlava.xyratex.com/show_bug.cgi?id=16308.\n\nCaller calls a LNetPut but destination still inaccessible and lnet don't able to release a TX and send an event for ptlrpc. Request hold an import reference and it prohibit an release obd device reference and broke a shutdown.\n\nPatch adds additional flag and forbid to access to the outgoing buffer and delay call interpret function (decrease an inflight rpc count) until both buffers (outgonning and incoming) and bulk buffer will released.\nrq_req_unlink == 0 indicate and buffer still unreleased, and ptlrpc_client_recv_or_unlink return true if recv or unlink process in flight.\nso\nptlrpc_unregister_reply via ptlrpc_client_recv_or_unlink vill forbid to call after_reply function (and modify outgoning buffer with MSG_RECOVERY flag) or prevent decrease an imp_in_flight checked in invalidate import function.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "584d0db032d0adbb314d26a12d4b76003d886f75",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-06 14:58:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nthanks for explaining, I see it now, so this change is about preventing request to be completed (and release refcount on imp_inflight) if LNet/LND still has refcount on request buffer, yes it makes sense. \nIt could be helpful to add some comments to explain rq_req_unlink and rq_reply_unlink (or give them better name). it's even better if you can copy some of these explanations to commit message :-), as all reviewers got confused about purpose of this patch. \nThanks again.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "abdee9f8cae72f9a5a9f7e9631de4c2448c438e7",
